    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl124_LabelType\">When you were too young to fight, you witnessed a great tragedy befall an innocent and you swore to Trudd you&rsquo;d become strong enough to prevent something like that from happening again.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTraits_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl124_LabelType\">Trudd</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl124_LabelType\">Once per day when you hit a foe with a melee attack, you can attempt an aid another action as a free action to increase an adjacent ally&rsquo;s AC against that foe. If you succeed, you grant the ally a +4 bonus to AC instead of a +2 bonus for that round.<br /></span></p>",
